thread.title: Jordan Spieth, Jason Day lead Presidents Cup teams
thread.title_full: Jordan Spieth, Jason Day lead Presidents Cup teams

author: tennessean
title: Jordan Spieth, Jason Day lead Presidents Cup teams
text:
Internationals
Sangmoon Bae, South Korea*
Age: 29
2014-15 PGA TOUR record: 30 events, 5 top-10 finishes, including 1 win (Frys.com Open)
Presidents Cup appearances: First appearance
Chip-in : Will represent the host country at the first Presidents Cup played in Asia. Bae became the fourth South Korean-born player to win on the PGA Tour when he won 2013 Byron Nelson Championship. He has won two professional events at Jack Nicklaus Golf Club Korea, site of this year’s Presidents Cup.
Steven Bowditch, Australia*
Age: 32
2014-15 PGA TOUR record: 32 events, 2 top-10 finishes, including win at AT&T Byron Nelson
Presidents Cup appearances: First appearance
Chip-in : Has won each of the past two PGA Tour seasons (both in his adopted home state of Texas).
USA TODAY
Phil Mickelson's Presidents Cup selection raises eyebrows, but players back him
Jason Day, Australia
Age: 27
2014-15 PGA TOUR record: 20 events, 11 top-10 finishes, including 5 wins (Farmers Insurance Open, RBC Canadian Open, PGA Championship, The Barclays, BMW Championship)
The Presidents Cup appearances (record): 2011, 2013 (4-4-2)
Chip-in: Finished in the top 10 in the year’s final three majors, including T9 while battling vertigo at the U.S. Open and T4 at The Open Championship, where he finished one shot outside of the playoff won by Zach Johnson. Set a record for lowest score in relation to par at a major championship, shooting 20-under 268 to beat Jordan Spieth by three at the PGA Championship.
Branden Grace, South Africa
Age: 27
2014-15 PGA TOUR record: 13 events, 4 top-10 finishes, including third place at the PGA Championship
The Presidents Cup appearances (record): 2013 (0-4-0)
Chip-in : Grace won twice in 2015, at the Dimension Data Pro-Am in his native South Africa and the European Tour’s Qatar Masters. He also finished in the top five at the U.S. Open and PGA Championship.
Thongchai Jaidee, Thailand
Age: 45
2014-15 PGA TOUR record : 10 events, including T34 at the World Golf Championships-Cadillac Match Play
Presidents Cup appearances (record): First appearance
Chip-in: First player from Thailand to qualify for Presidents Cup. Regarded as one of Asia’s greatest players, thanks to an unprecedented three Asian Tour Order of Merit crowns and 13 career victories.
USA TODAY
J.B. Holmes excited to step in for U.S. team at Presidents Cup
Anirban Lahiri, India
Age: 28
2014-15 PGA TOUR record: 12 events, including T5 at PGA Championship
Presidents Cup appearances (record): First appearance
Chip-in: Won twice on the European Tour this season, at the Hero Indian Open and Maybank Malaysian Open, helping him to become the first player from India to qualify for the Presidents Cup.
Danny Lee, New Zealand
Age: 25
2014-15 PGA TOUR record : 36 events, 8 top-10 finishes, including a win at The Greenbrier Classic
Presidents Cup appearances: First appearance
Chip-in: Earned his first PGA Tour title at The Greenbrier Classic, starting a strong stretch that boosted him onto his first International Presidents Cup team. He followed his win with three top-six finishes in his next four starts. When he won the 2008 U.S. Amateur at Pinehurst No. 2, he broke Tiger Woods’ record as the tournament’s youngest champion.
Marc Leishman, Australia
Age: 31
2014-15 PGA TOUR record: 23 events, 4 top-10 finishes, including T2 at The Open Championship
Presidents Cup appearances (record): 2013 (2-2-0)
Chip-in: Shot 14-under 130 (64-66) on the weekend at the British Open and lost in a three-man playoff to Johnson. Finished in the top 10 in two World Golf Championships, the Cadillac Match Play (T9) and HSBC Champions (ninth).
Hideki Matsuyama, Japan
Age: 23
2014-15 PGA TOUR record: 25 events, 9 top-10 finishes, including T2 at the Waste Management Open
Presidents Cup appearances (record): 2013 (1-3-1)
Chip-in: Finished third at the Frys.com Open and Hyundai Tournament of Champions. He also finished fifth at the Masters, his career-best finish in a major.
Louis Oosthuizen tees off at the 17th during his second round on the third day of the 144th Open Championship at St. Andrews - Old Course. (Photo: Ian Rutherford, USA TODAY Sports)
Louis Oosthuizen, South Africa
Age: 32
2014-15 PGA TOUR record: 20 events, 6 top-10 finishes, including a T2 at the U.S. Open and the British Open
Presidents Cup appearances (record): 2013 (1-3-1)
Chip-in: Joined the long line of South Africans who have won major championships when he won the 2010 Open Championship at St. Andrews by seven shots. Was runner-up at this year’s U.S. Open and British Open.
Charl Schwartzel, South Africa
Age: 31
2014-15 PGA TOUR record: 19 events, 3 top-10 finishes, including T3 at the Wyndham Championship
Presidents Cup appearances (record): 2011, 2013 (5-4-1)
Chip-in: Made the cut in all four majors, posting a seventh-place finish at the U.S. Open, where he shot a final-round 66.
Adam Scott, Australia
Age: 35
2014-15 PGA TOUR record: 15 events, 3 top-10 finishes, including T4 at the World Golf Championships-Cadillac Championship and U.S. Open
Presidents Cup appearances (record): 2003, 2005, 2007, 2009, 2011, 2013 (12-15-3)
Chip-in: The leader of the team, Scott has struggled this year. His FedExCup season ended at The Barclays, ending a streak of five consecutive appearances in The Tour Championship by Coca-Cola.
USA TODAY
Zach Johnson relishing opportunity to represent U.S. at Presidents Cup
USA
Rickie Fowler
Age: 26
2014-15 PGA TOUR record: 21 events, 7 top-10 finishes, including wins at The Players Championship and Deutsche Bank Championship
Presidents Cup appearances: First appearance
Chip-in: Played last six holes in 6-under to earn spot in playoff at The Players and then made birdie on the 17th — his third birdie on the hole that day — and won. Added victory in the Scottish Open on the European Tour.
Rickie Fowler lines up a putt on hole 9 as he finishes his first round at Conway Farms Golf Club. (Photo: Brian Spurlock, USA TODAY Sports)
Bill Haas*
Age: 33
2014-15 PGA TOUR record: 25 events, 5 top-10 finishes, including a win at the Humana Challenge in partnership with the Clinton Foundation
Presidents Cup appearances (record): 2011, 2013 (3-5-2)
Chip-in: Finished 11th in the standings and will play for his dad. Won the Humana Challenge for his sixth career PGA Tour title.
J.B. Holmes
Age: 33
2014-15 PGA TOUR record: 25 events, 7 top-10 finishes, including a win at the Shell Houston Open
Presidents Cup appearances : First appearance
Chip-in: Holmes replaced Jim Furyk, who could not play due to a wrist injury. Holmes finished 12th in the points standings. He was 2-0-1 in the 2008 Ryder Cup.
Dustin Johnson
Age: 31
2014-15 PGA TOUR record: 21 events, 11 top-10 finishes, including a win at the World Golf Championships-Cadillac Championship
Presidents Cup appearances (record): 2011 (1-3-1)
Chip-in: Won second World Golf Championships event at Doral to give him Tour titles in eight consecutive seasons. Three-putted final hole at U.S. Open to lose by one. Had miserable weekend after leading British Open after 36 holes. Concluded season with T5 at The Tour Championship.
Zach Johnson
Age : 39
2014-15 PGA TOUR record : 25 events, 10 top-10 finishes, including a win at The Open Championship
Presidents Cup appearances (record): 2007, 2009, 2013 (7-6-0)
Chip-in: Became the Championship Golfer of the Year with a playoff win in the British Open and only the sixth player to win major championships at St. Andrews and Augusta National (2007 Masters).
Chris Kirk
Age: 30
2014-15 PGA TOUR record : 21 events, 3 top-10 finishes, including a win at the Crowne Plaza Invitational at Colonial
Presidents Cup appearances: First appearance
Chip-in: Drained clutch six-foot putt on 72nd hole to win the Colonial, his fourth Tour title. Broke a bone in his right hand during the summer and missed two months.
Matt Kuchar
Age: 37
2015 PGA TOUR record: 25 events, 7 top-10 finishes, including T2 at the Humana Challenge in partnership with the Clinton Foundation
Presidents Cup appearances (record): 2011, 2013 (4-5-1)
Chip-in: From 2010-2014, averaged nearly 10 top-10s a season (48 total), winning five of his seven career titles during that span.
Phil Mickelson*
Age: 45
2014-15 PGA TOUR record: 19 events, 3 top-10 finishes, including T2 at the Masters
Presidents Cup appearances (record): 1994, 1996, 1998, 2000, 2003, 2005, 2007, 2009, 2011, 2013 (20-16-11)
Chip-in: Was a captain’s pick with this year’s U.S. captain, Jay Haas, for the inaugural Presidents Cup in 1994. Is making 25th appearance as a member of a U.S. team, including his two Walker Cups, a World Amateur Team Championship, a Dunhill Cup and the Ryder Cup.
Patrick Reed
Age: 25
2014-15 PGA TOUR record: 27 events, 4 top-10 finishes, including a win at the Hyundai Tournament of Champions
Presidents Cup appearances : First appearance
Chip-in: Was one of the lone stars on the U.S. Ryder Cup team in 2014, going 3-0-1.
Jordan Spieth poses with his family and trophies after winning the final round of the Tour Championship by Coca-Cola at East Lake Golf Club. (Photo: Jason Getz-USA TODAY Sports)
Jordan Spieth
Age: 22
2014-15 PGA TOUR record: 25 events, 15 top-10 finishes, including wins at the Valspar Championship, Masters, U.S. Open, John Deere Classic and Tour Championship by Coca-Cola
Presidents Cup appearances (record) : 2013 (2-2-0)
Chip-in: The world No. 1 had the best year in golf, winning his first two majors. A lucrative one, too, topping $22 million in earnings (including his $10 million bonus for winning the FedExCup). The youngest winner of the FedExCup is the best putter on the planet and was the youngest U.S. player in history of the Presidents Cup in 2013.
Jimmy Walker
Age: 36
2014-15 PGA TOUR record: 24 events, 6 top-10 finishes, including wins at the Sony Open in Hawaii and Valero Texas Open
Presidents Cup appearances : First appearance
Chip-in: After a torrid start to the season, he hasn’t had a top-10 since May in a PGA Tour event. Made Ryder Cup debut in 2014 and went 1-1-3.
Bubba Watson
Age: 36
2014-15 PGA TOUR record: 19 events, 10 top-10 finishes, including wins at the World Golf Championships-HSBC Champions and Travelers Championship
Presidents Cup appearances (record): 2011 (3-2-0)
Chip-in : The two-time Masters champion added two more wins this season. Is 5-1 in playoffs on PGA Tour. Has seven top-3 finishes this year.
* Captain’s selection
